{"title_page": "Alpha Centauri", "text_new": "{{hatnote|For other uses, see [[Alpha Centauri (disambiguation)]]. \"\u03b1 Centauri\" redirects here. It is not to be confused with [[HD 125823|a Centauri]] or [[A Centauri]]. \"Toliman\" redirects here. For other uses, see [[Toliman (disambiguation)]].}}\n{{short description|Star system}}\n{{Starbox begin\n | name = Alpha Centauri AB<ref group=note>[[Proxima Centauri]] is gravitationally bound to the \u03b1 Centauri system, but for practical and historical reasons it is described in detail in its own article.</ref>\n}}\n{{Starbox image\n| image = [[File:Alpha, Beta and Proxima Centauri (1).jpg|320px]]\n| caption = {{longitem|Alpha Centauri AB is the bright star to the left, which forms a triple star system with [[Proxima Centauri]], circled in red. The bright star system to the right is [[Beta Centauri]]. | style=font-size: 1em; padding: 4px 0;}}<!-- Please do not change. The two bright stars are Alpha and Beta, not just A and B. -->\n}}\n{{Starbox observe 2s\n| epoch = [[J2000.0]]\n| constell = [[Centaurus]]\n| component1 = Alpha Centauri A\n| ra1 = {{RA|14|39|36.49400}}<ref name=\"hipparcos\">{{cite journal\n| bibcode = 2007A&A...474..653V\n| title   = Validation of the new Hipparcos reduction\n| journal = Astronomy and Astrophysics\n| volume  = 474\n| issue   = 2\n| pages   = 653\u2013664\n| last1 = Van Leeuwen\n| first1  = F.\n| year    = 2007\n| doi     = 10.1051/0004-6361:20078357\n| arxiv   = 0708.1752\n}}</ref>\n| dec1={{DEC|\u221260|50|02.3737}}<ref name=\"hipparcos\" />\n| appmag_v1 = +0.01<ref name=\"ducati\">{{cite journal\n| bibcode = 2002yCat.2237....0D\n| title   = VizieR Online Data Catalog: Catalogue of Stellar Photometry in Johnson's 11-color system\n| journal = CDS/ADC Collection of Electronic Catalogues\n| volume  = 2237\n| pages   = 0\n| last1 = Ducati\n| first1  = J. R.\n| year    = 2002\n}}</ref>\n| component2 = Alpha Centauri B\n| ra2 = {{RA|14|39|35.06311}}<ref name=\"hipparcos\" />\n| dec2 = {