ce=J/A+A/341/121&HIP=71683\n| title      = HIP 71683\n| work       = Visual binary orbits and masses post Hipparcos\n| last1      = S\u00f6derhjelm\n| first1     = Staffan\n| year       = 1999\n| accessdate = 9 May 2014\n}}</ref>\n|-\n| van Leeuwen (2007) (A)\n| {{val|754.81|4.11}}\n| {{val|1.325|0.007}}\n| {{val|4.321|0.024|0.023}}\n| {{val|40.88|0.22}}\n|<ref name=\"van Leeuwen2007_A\">{{cite web\n| url   = http://webviz.u-strasbg.fr/viz-bin/VizieR-5?-source=I/311&HIP=71683\n| title = HIP 71683\n| work  = Validation of the new Hipparcos reduction\n| last  = van Leeuwen\n| first = Floor\n| year  = 2007\n}}</ref>\n|-\n| van Leeuwen (2007) (B)\n| {{val|796.92|25.90}}\n| {{val|1.25|0.04}}\n| {{val|4.09|0.14|0.13}}\n| 37.5 \u00b1 2.5\n|<ref name=\"van Leeuwen2007_B\">{{cite web\n| url   = http://webviz.u-strasbg.fr/viz-bin/VizieR-5?-source=I/311&HIP=71681\n| title = HIP 71681\n| work  = Validation of the new Hipparcos reduction\n| last  = van Leeuwen\n| first = Floor\n| year  = 2007\n}}</ref>\n|-\n| RECONS TOP100 (2012)\n| {{val|747.23|1.17}}<ref group=\"note\">Weighted parallax based on parallaxes from van Altena ''et al.'' (1995) and S\u00f6derhjelm (1999).</ref>\n| {{val|1.3383|0.0021}}\n| {{val|4.365|0.007}}\n| {{val|41.29|0.06}}\n|<ref name=\"RECONS\">{{cite web\n| work        = [[Research Consortium On Nearby Stars]]\n| publisher   = [[Georgia State University]]\n| date        = 7 September 2007\n| title       = The One Hundred Nearest Star Systems\n| url         = http://www.astro.gsu.edu/RECONS/TOP100.posted.htm\n| accessdate  = 2 December 2014\n| archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20071112173559/http://www.chara.gsu.edu/RECONS/TOP100.posted.htm\n| archivedate = 12 November 2007\n| url-status     = live\n}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n{{Portal|Astronomy|Star}}\n* [[Alpha Centauri in fiction]]\n* [[List of nearest stars and brown dwarfs]]\n* [[Project Longshot]]\n* [[Sagan Planet Walk]]\n\n== Notes ==\n{{Reflist|group=\"note\"}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|Alpha Centauri}}\n* [http://simbad.u-strasbg.fr/sim-id.pl?protocol=html&Ident=alpha+centauri SIMBAD observational data]\n* [http://ad.usno.navy.mil/wds/orb6.html Sixth Catalogue of Orbits of Visual Binary Stars U.S.N.O.]\n* [http://www.southastrodel.com/PageAlphaCen001.htm The Imperial Star&nbsp;\u2013 Alpha Centauri]\n* [http://www.southastrodel.com/PageAlphaCen006.htm Alpha Centauri&nbsp;\u2013 A Voyage to Alpha Centauri]\n* [http://www.southastrodel.com/PageAlphaCen006.htm Immediate History of Alpha Centauri]\n* [http://www.glyphweb.com/esky/stars/alphacentauri.html eSky : Alpha Centauri]\n\n=== Hypothetical planets or exploration ===\n* {{cite journal\n| title      = A Family Portrait of the Alpha Centauri System\n| pages       = 5\n| journal       = SpaceRef.com\n| url        = http://www.spaceref.com/news/viewpr.html?pid=11016\n| accessdate = 21 March 2003\n| bibcode       = 2003eso..pres....5.\n| year       = 2003\n}}\n* [http://jumk.de/astronomie/near-stars/alpha-centauri.shtml Alpha Centauri System]\n* [http://www.uranometrianova.pro.br/astronomia/AA002/alphacen.htm O Sistema Alpha Centauri (Portuguese)]\n* [http://www.alpha-centauri.pt/ Alpha Centauri&nbsp;\u2013 Associa\u00e7\u00e3o de Astronomia (Portuguese)]\n* {{cite news\n| last        = Thompson\n| first       = Andrea\n| date        = 7 March 2008\n| title       = Nearest Star System Might Harbor Earth Twin\n| publisher   = SPACE.com\n| url         = http://www.space.com/scienceastronomy/080307-another-earth.html\n| accessdate  = 17 July 2008\n| archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20080602011008/http://www.space.com/scienceastronomy/080307-another-earth.html\n| archivedate = 2 June 2008\n| url-status     = dead\n}}\n\n{{Sky|14|39|36.4951|-|60|50|02.308|4}}\n{{Alpha Centauri}}\n{{Nearest systems|1}}\n{{Stars of Centaurus}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2019}}\n{{EngvarO|date=September 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=February 2017}}\n\n